{
  "stem": "24195.4",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Nobody had them.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was quite an advance.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, this was 1944, 1945, toward the end the war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's why I couldn't understand when-- we always thought, how can they fly, how can they fight enemy planes that are propeller driven, because they are so much slower.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "These jets were flying 400, 500 miles like the jets today.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And how much do the regular B-17s and the Mustang planes-- they were all propeller planes.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So every time the air raid sirens would go on, all those guys scrambled into their planes and took off and flew east instead of west.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Instead of leading the oncoming-- I couldn't understand that, but I found later through William Shirer's book about D-Day, and so forth, he has-- they did-- they did use some of those jets.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And apparently, they were quite successful even though they are so much faster.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because by the time they have zeroed in on a target-- propelled plane-- they had already passed it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they apparently downed some of the Allied planes, even with those jets.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But normally, they just took off.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To keep them from being destroyed if the airport is attacked, which happened.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That satisfaction we got before it all ended.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know-- at the-- toward the-- it was like in early April, they were getting a-- every day there were air raids.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And every day we would interrupt our work and seek shelter, duck into trenches.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And looking up to the sky, we see those.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And those planes in World War II, they were only flying at 10,000 feet or less than that because that was the height.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "See those B-17s and then the fighter planes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And every day, every time this happened, we were wondering when will it be?",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
